article.description: Phlandrous Fleming Jr. had career highs of 34 points and 15 rebounds as Charleston Southern topped Hampton 85-72 on Saturday.
article.headline: Fleming leads Charleston Southern past Hampton 85-72
article.linkText: Fleming leads Charleston Southern past Hampton 85-72
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Phlandrous Fleming Jr. had career highs of 34 points and 15 rebounds as Charleston Southern topped Hampton 85-72 on Saturday. Fleming went over 1,000 career points and added five assists and three blocks. Deontaye Buskey matched his career high of 21 points for the Buccaneers (12-12, 6-6 Big South Conference). Fleming, Buskey and Nate Louis, who scored 10 points, each made 3-pointers. Charleston Southern shot 51 percent overall and was 10 of 28 from the arc. Ben Stanley, who came in as the nation's seventh-highest scorer at 22.4, had 20 points for the Pirates (10-13, 5-5). Jermaine Marrow added 19 points. Davion Warren had 18 points and nine rebounds. The Buccaneers evened the season series against the Pirates with the win. Hampton defeated Charleston Southern 92-85 on Jan. 4. Charleston Southern matches up against South Carolina Upstate on the road on Monday.
